This paper deals with wireless power transfer in ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and mobile agents (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the optimization of the charging range, which involves control and optimization (cs.SY) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents heuristics for addressing performance trade-offs, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
